Three miles uphill, three down .

contributions.title: Anything is possible!

contributions.title: bringing the magic to 10.5k
contributions.text: My twin sister and I have started dressing up for runs, mostly in Luxembourg but we also travel to loads of other races. People here do not really dress up for races and are all very serious, but we want to change this. Making people smile during runs and having a good time just make running much better. We're the Fancy Pantsy Runners :)

contributions.title: First race in three years!  Tracy Trapp
contributions.text: This is me on Sunday running in the Wingham 10K. It is the first race I have entered since being diagnosed with bilateral breast cancer in 2013. I was training for the VLM at the time but had to pull out.  I kept my running up through out my grueling treatment but didn't have the confidence to race until now... Picture by G O Siodhachain  Tracy x
